rest_of_day_open: I see myself going food shopping at the dollar store. Money is scarce now. We are running low on beans and rice. I'll need to buy some eggs so I can make noodles. I would like to get a hold of some bacon, which I can buy at the Dollar General and an onion, which I cannot.
critical_positive: When she was talking about herself, her education, and her family. We stuttered a bit starting out, but once we introduced ourselves by first name, we relaxed into the conversation. She is very young, so talking about her schooling and my youngest son seemed to do the trick. Education is expensive.
critical_negative: Like I said already, she is very young. I felt the conversation was artificial. If we met in line at a coffee place or whatever, we probably would not have spoken. I believe we were both in it for the money. We didn't cover a wide range of topics, it was difficult to change topics or start new ones.
employ_7_TEXT: Self employed as a rancher and writer

rest_of_day_open: I think my week will be pretty laid back. I don't have a ton of work due next week, so I will have some free time this weekend and after my classes on Thursday and Friday. Hopefully, I'll be able to catch up on some sleep this weekend as well.
critical_positive: We were both willing to talk to each other. She was very sweet and was open and offered a lot of information and insight about her life. We also had some in common, like our families and things we liked to do. She was also very respectful and we each had equal time to talk.
critical_negative: There was a significant age difference, but that didn't really impact me as much as it did her. Her life and location weren't as similar to mine either, but I was able to understand her experiences. Overall, she was awesome and there actually weren't any negative aspects of our conversation.
